MySQL is a relational database management system (RDBMS) that allows users to store, manage, and retrieve structured data. It's an open-source, cross-platform database product that uses structured query language (SQL) to organize data into tables. MySQL is used in many applications, including small-scale projects, large-scale websites, and enterprise-level solutions. It's often associated with web applications and online publishing, and is used by many of the top websites in the world, including Facebook, Twitter, and YouTube.